      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house in Toronto, is essentially a temporary holding place for funds and documents, usually managed by a neutral third party, like a lawyer or a real estate professional. Think of it like a secure, temporary holding pen for your money and the paperwork until all the conditions of the sale are met. It's crucial because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the funds are only released once the property transfer is legally complete. This prevents any shady dealings, which is vital when you're dealing with such a big transaction.",
